00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:04,091
WITH A SOLUTION TO THE DREADED
CHORE OF DOING LAUNDRY.

00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:07,127
♪♪

00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,402
HEY, SHARKS,
MY NAME IS MAXWELL COHEN.

00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:18,472
I'M FROM NEW YORK CITY,
AND MY COMPANY IS AfreSHeet.

00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:23,110
I'M SEEKING $100,000 IN EXCHANGE
FOR 20% OF MY BUSINESS.

00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:25,145
LYDIA HERE, SHE'S A BUSY WOMAN.

00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:26,580
SHE'S A FULL-TIME
COLLEGE STUDENT,

00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:28,482
HAS A PART-TIME JOB
IN THE EVENING.

00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:30,517
WHO HAS TIME
TO WASH THEIR SHEETS?
[ LAUGHS ]

00:02:30,517 --> 00:02:32,586
DORM BEDS ARE USED
FOR MORE THAN JUST SLEEPING.

00:02:32,586 --> 00:02:36,189
THEY'RE USED AS A KITCHEN,
A DESK, A DINING ROOM TABLE --

00:02:36,189 --> 00:02:37,257
PRETTY MUCH EVERYTHING.

00:02:37,257 --> 00:02:40,494
LUCKILY FOR LYDIA,
SHE SLEEPS ON AfreSHeet.

00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:44,297
AfreSHeet'S THE WORLD'S FIRST
AND ONLY FITTED BED SHEET

00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:47,134
WITH PEEL-AWAY
DISPOSABLE TOP LAYERS.

00:02:47,134 --> 00:02:48,969
WHEN YOU SOIL YOUR BED...

00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:53,674
...YOU PEEL OFF THAT LAYER

00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:57,444
TO INSTANTLY REVEAL A BRAND-NEW
LAYER BENEATH.

00:02:57,444 --> 00:02:59,946
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:02:59,946 --> 00:03:00,580
OH, AND THIS MESS?

00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:02,816
YOU THROW IT RIGHT
IN THE RECYCLING BIN.

00:03:02,816 --> 00:03:06,720
HEY, IF THERE HAPPENS TO BE
ANOTHER MESS, DO NOT PANIC.

00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:10,924
AfreSHeet'S GOT SEVEN PEEL-AWAY,
DISPOSABLE TOP LAYERS.

00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:17,197
THERE IS SO MANY DIFFERENT USES
FOR AfreSHeet, SO MOM,

00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:18,331
DON'T SEND YOUR KID OFF
TO COLLEGE

00:03:18,331 --> 00:03:20,033
HOPING ONE DAY
THEY'LL WASH THEIR SHEET.

00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:20,701
AfreSHeet.

00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:23,203
TODDLER'S NOT FEELING WELL
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT?

00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:24,204
AfreSHeet.

00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,506
FRIEND'S COMING TO VISIT?
AfreSHeet.

00:03:26,506 --> 00:03:28,842
SHARKS, I STARTED THIS COMPANY
WHILE I WAS IN COLLEGE

00:03:28,842 --> 00:03:31,645
AND I'VE POURED A LOT OF BLOOD,
SWEAT, AND TEARS INTO THIS
BUSINESS.

00:03:31,645 --> 00:03:36,049
FORTUNATELY FOR ME, I CAN PEEL
IT ALL AWAY WITH AfreSHeet.

00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,484
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:03:37,484 --> 00:03:39,219
O'Leary:
MAXWELL, WHAT'S IT MADE OF?

00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,687
IT IS MADE OUT
OF POLYESTER.

00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:43,323
DO YOU HAVE SAMPLES
FOR US TO TOUCH?
OF COURSE.

00:03:43,323 --> 00:03:45,459
MAX, POLYESTER
DOESN'T BREATHE.

00:03:45,459 --> 00:03:48,361
SO, THIS IS THE NEWEST VERSION
OF THE SHEET.

00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:51,198
THIS IS MADE OUT OF THREE
DIFFERENT TYPES OF POLYESTER.

00:03:51,198 --> 00:03:53,433
IT DOESN'T FEEL GREAT.

00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:56,036
DON'T PEOPLE WANT
A SOFT SHEET TO SLEEP ON?

00:03:56,036 --> 00:03:57,471
THIS FEELS CLINICAL.

00:03:57,471 --> 00:04:00,607
WE'RE NOT COMPETING
WITH EGYPTIAN COTTON.

00:04:00,607 --> 00:04:03,310
WE ARE HERE FOR PRACTICALITY
AND CONVENIENCE.

00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:05,345
BUT IT DOESN'T BREATHE,
RIGHT?

00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:06,747
IT IS VERY BREATHABLE.
[ BLOWS ]

00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:09,416
SO, IT'S NOT AS BREATHABLE
AS CONVENTIONAL BED SHEETS.
IT'S NOT BREATHING, MAX.

00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,550
THERE'S NO WAY
I CAN BLOW THROUGH THIS.

00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:12,252
KEVIN, IS THAT
A SCIENTIFIC TEST?
[ BLOWS ]

00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,420
-YEAH.
-IT IS.

00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:14,688
IT'S SORT OF LIKE PAPER,
THOUGH,

00:04:14,688 --> 00:04:17,057
BECAUSE I JUST POKED
MY FINGER THROUGH IT.

00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:18,592
HOW MUCH DO YOU HAVE
IN SALES?

00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:19,693
Herjavec:
YEAH, WHAT HAVE YOU SOLD?

00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:22,496
SO, I'VE SOLD A LITTLE OVER
400 AfreSHeetS.

00:04:22,496 --> 00:04:24,431
-THE FIRST GENERATION --
-400,000?

00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:26,666
NO, 400.
WE'RE JUST A START-UP.

00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,268
-NO KIDDING.
-HOW MUCH DO YOU SELL THEM FOR?

00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:31,271
I SELL THEM FOR $29.95
FOR A TWIN EXTRA LONG.

00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:34,508
I COULD SEE A BIG MARKET
FOR IT, ACTUALLY.

00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:36,510
I MEAN, I'M SURPRISED
YOU HAVEN'T SOLD MORE.

00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,378
I COULD SEE IT IN HOSPITALS.
-YES.

00:04:38,378 --> 00:04:40,480
ANYWHERE WHERE THERE'S MORE
OF A CLINICAL APPLICATION.

00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:43,049
YEAH.
HAVE YOU APPROACHED
THOSE KIND OF MARKETS?

00:04:43,049 --> 00:04:45,152
WE'VE HAD A LOT OF INTEREST

00:04:45,152 --> 00:04:47,420
FROM SUMMER CAMPS,
ELDERLY HOMES.

00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:49,422
WE'RE IN THE WORKS WITH A BUNCH
OF THEM RIGHT NOW.

00:04:49,422 --> 00:04:52,392
WE WERE JUST
AT A GIANT COLLEGE EXPO.

00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:54,461
LOTS OF BUZZ.
-LOTS OF ORDERS?

00:04:54,461 --> 00:04:56,997
SO, WE'RE WAITING FOR THE NEWEST
SHIPMENT TO COME IN.

00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:58,398
IT IS ON ITS WAY.

00:04:58,398 --> 00:05:00,400
WE'RE ACTUALLY HELD UP
IN CUSTOMS RIGHT NOW.

00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,602
HOW MANY PEOPLE WROTE PURCHASE
ORDERS, THOUGH, AT THE SHOW?

00:05:02,602 --> 00:05:07,240
SO, WE'RE SUCH A NEW PRODUCT,
IT'S ONE OF THOSE IDEAS,

00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,542
IT'S -- YOU HAVE TO WRAP
YOUR HEAD AROUND IT.

00:05:08,542 --> 00:05:12,212
AND NOBODY'S CHANGED THE BED
SHEET FOR HUNDREDS OF YEARS.

00:05:12,212 --> 00:05:13,313
SO,
THEY DIDN'T ORDER.

00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,648
SO, NOT YET.

00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:18,385
HOW MUCH OF YOUR OWN MONEY
IS INTO THIS COMPANY?

00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:21,087
SO, I INVESTED
TO START THIS BUSINESS

00:05:21,087 --> 00:05:22,289
ALL OF MY BAR MITZVAH MONEY.

00:05:22,289 --> 00:05:23,557
HOW MUCH WAS THAT?

00:05:23,557 --> 00:05:25,625
I HAD ABOUT
A LITTLE OVER $12,000.

00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:29,262
WOW.
WHAT'S IT COST YOU
TO MAKE ONE $29.95 PACKAGE?

00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:31,364
THAT ONE
IS A LITTLE OVER $7.

00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:33,333
WE'RE WORKING ON NEW BETTER
MATERIALS THAT ARE --

00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,568
MAX,
THERE'S VERY MANY LARGE

00:05:34,568 --> 00:05:36,469
BIG-BOX RETAILERS
THAT SELL SHEETS.

00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:39,372
YEAH.
HAVE YOU SHOWN ANY
OF THEM THIS PRODUCT?

00:05:39,372 --> 00:05:42,209
SO, I PITCHED SOMEBODY
AT BED BATH &amp; BEYOND.
AND?

00:05:42,209 --> 00:05:43,577
THEY DIDN'T WANT
TO BE THE PEOPLE

00:05:43,577 --> 00:05:45,512
TO INTRODUCE IT TO THE WORLD.
-OOH.

00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:48,915
IT'S NOT AS SOFT
AS THEY WANT IT TO BE.

00:05:48,915 --> 00:05:49,516
HMM.

00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:52,185
SO, EVERYBODY LOVES THE IDEA,

00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:54,321
AND SAID
"THE IDEA IS BRILLIANT."

00:05:54,321 --> 00:05:55,355
THEY SAID THE IDEA
IS BRILLIANT.

00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:56,423
YEAH, BUT YOUR BUSINESS
IS NOT RETAIL.

00:05:56,423 --> 00:05:58,291
-YOUR BUSINESS IS INSTITUTIONAL.
-RIGHT.

00:05:58,291 --> 00:06:00,393
SO, OVERSEAS,
WE'VE HAD A LOT OF INTEREST.

00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:02,429
WE'VE BEEN
IN SOUTH AFRICAN HOSPITALS

00:06:02,429 --> 00:06:04,531
AND SOUTH AFRICAN AMBULANCES.

00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:06,466
IN AMERICA, WE'RE NOT PUSHING
TOWARDS HOSPITALS --

00:06:06,466 --> 00:06:09,069
HOW BIG IS THE SOUTH AFRICAN
AMBULANCE MARKET?

00:06:09,069 --> 00:06:10,570
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:06:10,570 --> 00:06:13,540
MAX, YOU'RE FEELING YOUR WAY IN
AND YOU'RE LEARNING AS YOU GO,

00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,109
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU'RE READY FOR AN INVESTMENT,

00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:17,210
AND CERTAINLY NOT
MY MONEY.

00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,478
WITH THAT SAID, I'M OUT.

00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:21,181
-HE'S OUT. THANK YOU.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

00:06:21,181 --> 00:06:22,515
Herjavec: MAX,
SOMETIMES PEOPLE COME OUT

00:06:22,515 --> 00:06:25,452
AND I THINK, "WOW,
I'VE NEVER SEEN THAT BEFORE."

00:06:25,452 --> 00:06:28,488
IS IT BRILLIANT
OR IS IT NOT?

00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:29,589
WHICH ONE IS THIS,
ROBERT?

00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:31,524
I KNOW YOU'RE COMPARING IT
TO COTTON SHEETS

00:06:31,524 --> 00:06:33,360
AND ALL THAT,
BUT THAT'S NOT HIS MARKET.

00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,061
I MEAN,
I'VE GOT KIDS AT COLLEGE.

00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:36,162
THEIR SHEETS ARE A MESS.

00:06:36,162 --> 00:06:37,564
THEY WOULD BUY IT
AND RIP IT OFF.

00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,366
I COULD SEE
ELDERLY HOMES.

00:06:39,366 --> 00:06:40,500
WHY AREN'T THOSE PEOPLE
BUYING IT?

00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,202
'CAUSE, TO ME,
IT SEEMS LIKE A SLAM DUNK.

00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:43,937
YOU KNOW WHY
THEY'RE NOT BUYING IT, MAX?

00:06:43,937 --> 00:06:45,038
IT'S A DOG.

00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:46,139
I LOVE DOGS.

00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:47,340
MAX, I'M GONNA
HELP YOU OUT HERE.

00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:48,441
I HATE IT.

00:06:48,441 --> 00:06:50,176
-PERFECT.
-I'M OUT.

00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:51,344
SHOOT IT, BURN IT,
GET RID OF IT,

00:06:51,344 --> 00:06:52,479
DO SOMETHING ELSE
WITH YOUR TIME.

00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:54,414
I APPRECIATE IT.
THANK YOU.

00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:57,817
IF IT WAS SOFT
AND COMFORTABLE.

00:06:57,817 --> 00:07:00,620
LIKE YOU SAID...
IT WOULD BE CALLED A SHEET
MADE OF COTTON.

00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:03,356
...YOU WERE NEXT TO A BOOTH
THAT PROBABLY WAS MICRO FLEECE.

00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:05,191
I LIKE SOMETHING
REALLY SOFT.

00:07:05,191 --> 00:07:06,726
PEOPLE GO INTO THEIR BEDS
FOR COMFORT.

00:07:06,726 --> 00:07:08,628
PEOPLE KNOW THEY HAVE
TO WASH THEIR SHEETS

00:07:08,628 --> 00:07:10,964
BUT THEY DON'T
BECAUSE THEY'RE LAZY.

00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,200
LORI,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,736
I'M OUT.

00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:20,206
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T BELIEVE IN THE CONCEPT.

00:07:20,206 --> 00:07:22,242
I'M OUT.

00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:25,478
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES,
CUSTOMERS LIE TO YOU.

00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:28,548
THE BEST WAY TO GET RID OF
A SALESMAN IS TO TELL THEM WHAT?

00:07:28,548 --> 00:07:30,583
-HOW TO GET RID OF A SALESMAN?
-YEAH.

00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:33,420
YOU ACT LIKE MR. WONDERFUL
AND TELL THEM THEY'RE TERRIBLE.

00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:35,422
NO.
NO, BECAUSE THEN
THEY KEEP OBJECTING.

00:07:35,422 --> 00:07:36,690
THE BEST WAY
TO GET RID OF A SALESMAN

00:07:36,690 --> 00:07:38,758
IS TO TELL THEM WHAT
THEY THINK THEY WANT TO HEAR --

00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:41,261
THAT THEY MIGHT
BE GETTING AN ORDER.
GOT IT.

00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:42,696
YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY ORDERS.

00:07:42,696 --> 00:07:45,498
YOU'VE TESTED THE MARKET AND
THE MARKET'S SPEAKING TO YOU.

00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:46,700
OH, THEY LOVE IT.
THEY LOVE IT.

00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,601
-PEOPLE LOVE IT.
-WELL, NO, THEY DON'T LOVE IT.

00:07:48,601 --> 00:07:51,938
THEY'RE NOT BEING GENEROUS.
IF THEY LOVED IT,
THEY WOULD BUY IT.

00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:55,909
I GOT TO GO OUT BECAUSE
THE MARKET'S TELLING YOU THAT.

00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,511
-THAT'S IT.
-THAT'S IT. THANKS, GUYS.

00:07:58,511 --> 00:08:00,313
-GOOD LUCK. APPRECIATE IT.
-GOOD LUCK.

00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,382
MAX, SHOOT IT.

00:08:02,382 --> 00:08:03,450
-YOU LOVE IT.
-BEHIND THE BARN.

00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:05,085
-THANKS, MR. WONDERFUL.
-MAX, THANK YOU.

00:08:05,085 --> 00:08:06,519
-BYE.
-MAX, GOOD LUCK.

00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:09,589
Cohen: I BELIEVE THIS IS
AN IDEA OF A LIFETIME.

00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:12,092
IS IT A LITTLE HEARTBREAKING?
YEAH.

00:08:12,092 --> 00:08:13,560
IS IT THEIR LOSS?
YEAH.

00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,096
AM I EXCITED FOR THE FUTURE?
OH, YEAH.

